  "text": "Some text-first approaches treat parsing and disfluency detection jointly, though the models differ in the type of parse formalism employed. [CITATION_1] use a PCFG-based parser to parse sentences along with finding edited phrases. [CITATION_2] use a right-corner transform of binary branching structures on bracketed sentences but their results are much worse than [CITATION_3] . To date, none of the prior joint approaches have used a dependency formalism.",
